    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing Asaph's theological argument in its original Zion-Song context, its canonical resonances, and its New Testament fulfillments. The four movements below follow the psalm's own structure: proclamation of God's presence and power (76:1-3), narration of the divine victory (76:4-9), the governing theological principle (76:10), and the covenantal demand (76:11-12). Where Hebrew idiom sharpens meaning, a brief note follows.",
